{"lemma":"حَرَمَيْ","slug":"حَرَمَيْ","root":"ح.ر.م","root_slug":"ح-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَرَم","root":"حرم","pos":"V","occurrence_count":39},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":11,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":26},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7769","n7770","n7771"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be sacred, to be sacrosanct, to be inviolable"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be forbidden, to be prohibited, to be interdicted, to be unlawful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deprive, to dispossess, to divest, to bereave, to withhold, to withdraw, to deny, to refuse","examples":[{"text":"حُرِمَ ٱلطِّفْلُ مِنْ أُمِّهِ.","english":"The child was taken away from his mother."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to exclude, to preclude"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to excommunicate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to declare sacred, to declare sacrosanct, to declare inviolable, to declare taboo"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to declare unlawful, to forbid, to interdict, to proscribe","examples":[{"text":"وَيُحِلُّ لَهُمُ الطَّيِّبَاتِ وَيُحَرِّمُ عَلَيْهِمُ الْخَبَائِثَ","english":"And he makes lawful for them the good things and prohibits for them the evil"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to immunize"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرَمَ (ḥarama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"excommunication"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pilgrim's cloak"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرُمَ (ḥaruma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything sacred"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pilgrim's cloak"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"forbidden, prohibited, interdicted"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"taboo"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"holy, sacred, sacrosanct"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرِمَ (ḥarima) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sacred object, sacred possession"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wife"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sanctum, sanctuary, sacred precinct","examples":[{"text":"اَلْحَرَمَيْن / اَلْحَرَمَان","english":"the two sanctuaries or sacred precincts (the two mosques or cities of Mecca and Medina)"},{"text":"ثَالِث الْحَرَمَيْن","english":"the third holiest site or pilgrimage destination (Jerusalem's Temple Mount)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حَرِيم (ḥarīm)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حَرَام (ḥarām)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of حَرَام (ḥarām)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرُمَ (ḥaruma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حُرْمَة (ḥurma)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew חֵרֶם (ḥērem, “taboo, consecration”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7769","headword_ar":"حَرْمَى","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a female cloven-hoofed animal, (K,) or to a ewe, or she-goat, (S,) and to a she-wolf and to a bitch, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Desiring the male:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiraAmN","text_ar":"حِرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAmaY","text_ar":"حَرَامَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EijaAlN","text_ar":"عِجَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajaAlaY","text_ar":"عَجَالَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or the latter pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuraAmaY","text_ar":"حُرَامَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (so accord. to some copies of the K [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EujaAlaY","text_ar":"عُجَالَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"];) as though its masc., if it had a masc., were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaromaAnu","text_ar":"حَرْمَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaromaY wa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَرْمَى وَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA wa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"اَمَا وَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"now surely, by God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HazomaY wa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَزْمَى وَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hzm","text_ar":"حزم"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n7770","headword_ar":"حِرْمِىٌّ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":": fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiromiy~apN","text_ar":"حِرْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, TA.) [In the TA it is said that Mbr mentions two forms of the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hrmy~p","text_ar":"حرميّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to a woman: it does not specify what these are; but one seems to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huromiy~apN","text_ar":"حُرْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for he says that it is from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa Huromapi Albayoti","text_ar":"وَ حُرْمَةِ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ by the sacredness of the House ” of God.] Az says, on the authority of Lth, that when they applied the rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaramu","text_ar":"الحَرَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to anything not a human being, [as, for instance, to a garment, or piece of cloth,] they said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN HaramiY~N","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ حَرَمِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) [but] they also said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiromiy~apN","text_ar":"حِرْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sihaAmN Hiromiy~apN","text_ar":"سِهَامٌ حِرْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arrows of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiromiy~apN","text_ar":"حِرْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN Hiromiy~apN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ حِرْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bow made of a tree of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 284.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose food was eaten by a pilgrim, and in whose clothes this pilgrim performed his circuiting round the Kaábeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pilgrim who ate the food of a man of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and performed his circuiting round the Kaábeh in this man's clothes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"each of these was called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiromiY~","text_ar":"حِرْمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the other: every one of the chiefs of the Arabs who imposed upon himself hardship, or strictness, in his religious practices had a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HrmY~","text_ar":"حرمىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the tribe of Kureysh; and when he performed the pilgrimage, would not eat any food but that of this man, nor perform his circuiting round the Kaabeh except in this man's clothes. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S"]},{"entry_id":"n7771","headword_ar":"حَرَمِىٌّ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}